OL,6,FFirst Contact Health also failed to
OL,7,Fintroduce further measures to prevent
OL,8,Funauthorised access, such as geo-
OL,9,Fblocking unusual IP addresses.
OL,11,FNext, the physiotherapist did not have
OL,12,Ftools which monitor suspicious
OL,13,Factivity, and so did not realise there
OL,14,Fhad been an attack for at least five
OL,15,Fmonths after it had occurred.
OL,17,FFinally, First Contact Health failed
OL,18,Fto conduct regular security audits or
OL,19,Fpenetration tests, which meant the
OL,20,Fabove problems were not flagged.
